  <front>
   <head>To the Honble. Miss Carteret, now Countess of Dysert.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Innocence, the Muses loveliest Theme!</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">On Acts of Mercy sound thy rising Fame.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let others from frail Beauty hope Applause:</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Plead thou the Fatherless, and Widow's Cause.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Fly to your Mother; let each winning Grace</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Engage Compassion for my helpless Race.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">So shall the wond'ring World be taught from thence,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Beauty is but your  Excellence.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
